\title{gs4mattr: Cell Formatting and Conditional Formatting for googlesheets4}
\description{
\code{gs4mattr} extends \code{googlesheets4} with a formatting layer for Google
Sheets. Function names and argument order mirror \code{googlesheets4}'s own
conventions (\verb{gs4_*} spreadsheet-level, \verb{sheet_*} worksheet-level,
\verb{range_*} range-level) so it behaves like a natural extension. It always
reuses whatever auth \code{googlesheets4::gs4_auth()} already has active — no
separate auth system.
}
\details{
Key functions:
\itemize{
\item \code{\link[=range_format]{range_format()}} / \code{\link[=range_format_border]{range_format_border()}} — basic cell formatting
\item \code{\link[=sheet_freeze]{sheet_freeze()}}, \code{\link[=sheet_format_header]{sheet_format_header()}}, \code{\link[=sheet_format_tabcolor]{sheet_format_tabcolor()}} — sheet-level structure
\item \code{\link[=range_merge]{range_merge()}} / \code{\link[=range_unmerge]{range_unmerge()}} — merged cells
\item \code{\link[=range_add_conditional_format]{range_add_conditional_format()}} + \code{\link[=cf_cell_value]{cf_cell_value()}} and friends — boolean conditional formatting
\item \code{\link[=range_add_gradient_format]{range_add_gradient_format()}} + \code{\link[=cf_gradient]{cf_gradient()}} — gradient conditional formatting
\item \code{\link[=range_write_format]{range_write_format()}} — write a data frame and format it in one call
\item \code{\link[=gs4mattr_batch]{gs4mattr_batch()}} — batch several formatting calls into one API request
}

Note: \code{googlesheets4::range_autofit()} already covers column/row
auto-sizing, and \code{googlesheets4::sheet_write()} already applies header
styling and freezes row 1 automatically — \code{gs4mattr} doesn't duplicate
either, and its own header/freeze helpers are meant as the manual
equivalent for data written with \code{range_write()} instead.

Also note: the Sheets API's conditional formatting only supports boolean
and gradient rules — there is no data-bar rule in the API (data bars are
a Sheets UI-only feature), so \code{gs4mattr} doesn't offer one.
